Quote:  JORDANiDiA SOLANDRi (Cuvier and Valenciennes). Southern Kingfish. Sold as `hake' in Wellington and `lemon-fish' in Auckland. Large quantities are taken by the trawlers from Napier southward. Common, South island. ... Distribution: Numbers taken during spring, Hauraki Gulf and Bay of Plenty (unknown, Bay of islands).
Notes:  Phillipps Notes on the Edible Fishes

